cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with automatic parsing of anatomical objects in X-ray images using deep learning models. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel framework for unsupervised domain adaptation, which involves generative modeling and adversarial training, and thus can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of Digitally Reconstructed Radiographs (DRRs) and CT scans also suggests a possible association with multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of pre-trained models and transfer learning techniques indicates a possible connection with neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
